# Local ignore rules for stray telemetry artifacts.
#
# The `TrackCommand::SetCommitHash` `items_dir()` accessor previously returned
# the CWD-relative "track/items" fallback, which could cause telemetry writes
# to land under apps/cli/track/ when the process ran from a subdirectory.
# That bug was fixed by making SetCommitHash discover the git repo root via
# `git rev-parse --show-toplevel` and return an absolute items_dir path.
#
# The root-level `.gitignore` rule `track/items/**/logs/` only matches paths
# anchored at the repo root. It does NOT cover `apps/cli/track/items/.../logs/`
# paths. This local rule covers any residual stray artifacts under this crate.
# The leading `/` anchors the pattern to `apps/cli/` so that the `src/commands/track/`
# source tree is not accidentally ignored.
/track/items/**/logs/
